<HEADLINE> Cambodia Gets Chinese Vehicles Under Loan Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia received 2.8
million U.S. dollars worth of vehicles on Tuesday under a loan
project signed with the Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony for the delivery of 116 trucks and 70 jeeps made in
China was attended by Cambodia's Second Prime Minister Hun Sen,
who expressed his gratitude for China's support.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia, now facing difficulties, appreciates China's aid for
its peace and reconstruction, Hun said, adding that the friendly
cooperative ties should be further promoted.
</P>
<P>
The vehicles are sent here as part of an agreement reached in
1994 on China's long-term interest-free loan to Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
China's Ambassador to Cambodia Yan Ting'ai also spoke at the
ceremony, saying he hoped the vehicles will play an active role in
Cambodia's economic recovery and development.
</P>
<P>
Lakhan L. Mehrotra, the United Nations Secretary-General's
Special Representative to Cambodia, attended the ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
