<HEADLINE> Canada's New Vehicle Sales Up 1.6 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 9 (Xinhua) -- New motor vehicle sales in
Canada rose 1.9 percent in October, following a 3.4 percent drop
in the previous month, Statistics Canada reported today.
</P>
<P>
In October, the country's new motor vehicle sales reached
118,705 units, up 12.5 percent from a year ago.
</P>
<P>
New truck sales, which include minivans and sport utility
vehicles, rose 6.1 percent to 59,671 units in October, while sales
of passenger cars slipped 2.0 percent to 59,034 units.
</P>
<P>
For the first time in 50 years, new truck sales accounted for
more than half of all new motor vehicles sold in Canada, the
statistics agency said.
</P>
<P>
New motor vehicle sales in Canada have generally increased
since April 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
