<HEADLINE> UNHCR Official Arrives in Addis Ababa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, Decemebr 9 (Xinhua) -- The Assistant High
Commissioner for Refugees, Viera De Mello, arrived here today
to discuss with Ethiopian officals refugee and humanitarian issues
in the region.
</P>
<P>
The assistant high commissioner was recently appointed as the
United Nations Under Secretary General for Humanitarian Affairs
and Emergency Relief Coordinator in the U.N.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued by the United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR), Mello is here to discuss
refugee and humanitarian issues in the region with Ethiopian
government officials, and officials from the Organization of
African Unity (OAU) and the United Nations Economic Commision for
Africa (ECA). He is also scheduled to discuss with Ethiopian
government officials the refugee situation in Ethiopia and the
joint government-UNHCR assistance and protection activities.
</P>
<P>
The refugee situation in Africa at present remains critical.
As of the beginning of this year, there were some six million
refugees in Africa as well as at least twice as many internally
displaced people.
</P>
<P>
The press release said, in cooperation with the OAU member
states, UNHCR and the international community have been working
to find lasting solution to the plight of refugees mostly through
voluntary repatriation, adding that many refugees have returned
to their home this year and it is hoped this trend will continue
in the year ahead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
