<HEADLINE> 7 Killed in Armed Clashes in North Mogadishu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were confirmed
dead and four others were wounded when armed clashes erupted
between rival militiamen supporting faction leader, Ali Mahdi
Mohamed, in North Mogadishu late this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
According to eyewitnesses, the fighting began when armed men
manning a checkpoint at a road junction in North Mogadishu have
shot and killed the driver of a public transport minibus where
also several others were wounded. The eyewitnesses also said two
more others were also killed in two different junctions in just
few moments.
</P>
<P>
Angry militiamen trying to take revenge
have attacked a garage in Karan district where the heaviest
clashes occurred following the excessive use of rocket propelled
grenades, recoilless rifles, heavy machine guns as well as
assault rifles, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, most of the dead were noncombatant
civilians that include two engineers, none of whom belonged to
the clansmen who were engaged in the fighting today.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the fighting is related to an earlier clashes
between the same two groups in Deganley village, 25 km north of
the capital, late last month. Reports said 15 people were killed
in the previous incident when the two groups argued over the
ownership of a farmland in the area.
</P>
<P>
The fighting has so far subsided as the darkness overshadowed
the area. However, angry militiamen remain in defensive position.
</P>
<P>
This incident is unfortunately taking place at a time when
all the Somali factions are meeting in Cairo for a possible
solution to Somalia's long-standing political crises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
