<HEADLINE> S. Africa's PPI Growth Drops to 26-year Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 9 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's producer
price inflation dropped in October to a 26-year low of 4.9
percent, the Central Statistics Service (CSS) said today.
</P>
<P>
The production price index (PPI) declined by 1.2 percentage
points from 6.1 percent in the same month a year ago. Its monthly
growth also slowed down to 0.2 percentage points, compared with
1.3 percentage points between September and October last year.
</P>
<P>
The PPI growth in October this year was significantly below
market expectations. Economists' estimates were at about 5.5
percent.
</P>
<P>
The annualized PPI for domestically produced goods declined by
0.8 percentage points to 5.7 percent, while the monthly index
slightly increased by 0.1 percentage points.
</P>
<P>
The yearly import inflation dropped to 1.3 percent from 3.8
percent in September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
