<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Twenty-Seven Percent Pregnant Women Drink Alcohol </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 9 (Xinhua) -- French women control less their
consumption of alcohol during pregnancy than those of other
European countries such as Britain and Spain, Agence France-Presse
(AFP) quoted some doctors specialized in alcohol problems as
saying today.
</P>
<P>
Consumption of alcohol by mothers during their pregnancy can
seriously affect the growth of body and intelligence of their
babies.
</P>
<P>
In France, 27 percent of pregnant women are exposed to the risk
of harming their children because of consumption of alcohol, as
compared with 5 percent in Britain and the Netherlands, and 3
percent in Spain, according to the doctors.
</P>
<P>
"Alcohol contained in drink passes very quickly into blood,
During the period of pregnancy, it goes across the placenta and
acts directly on the foetus," said the doctors.
</P>
<P>
The alcoholism syndrome of foetus cannot be observed but in
those born of mothers who drink an excessive amount of alcohol, or
more than six cups of alcohol a day, said the doctors.
</P>
<P>
France is among the countries of high per capita consumption of
alcohol, with 11.5 liters in average by each inhabitant in one
year.
</P>
<P>
Among 3.3 million French nationals who have a problem linked
with alcoholism are 600,000 women, according to the French
Committee for Education and Health, a national health information
organ. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
