<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Train Collision Injures at Least 30 People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 9 (Xinhua) -- At least 34 people were injured,
11 of them seriously, when a passenger train collided with a
diesel-loaded freight train near the northern German city of
Hannover late this afternoon, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
German police said that two of the freight train's 22 tank cars
exploded and sent off a huge fire after the head-on collision
occurred at about 16:50 local time. Parts of the passenger train
had been fully destroyed from the crash.
</P>
<P>
News reports quoted eyewitnesses as saying that many passengers
were wandering about the remote accident area in panic. About 400
policemen and firefighters had been involved in the rescue
operations. All ambulances available in Hannover had been sent to
the scene. 
</P>
</TEXT>
