</P>
<P>
Albright has invited Savimbi for a meeting in Luanda, capital
of Angola, on issues concerning the peace process. However, no
reply of certainty has been received so far, an official of the
U.S. Embassy said here.
</P>
<P>
Also today, Angolan congressmen told the local press that
Albright's forthcoming visit will inject fresh blood into the
Angolan peace process.
</P>
<P>
Pinto de Andrade, congressman of the ruling National
Liberation Movement of Angola, said Albright's visit on December
12 will impel the National Union for the Total Independence of
Angola (UNITA) to speed up its implementation of the peace accord
signed in 1994.
</P>
<P>
