of her visit will not be affected, for UNITA's representatives in
Luanda could convey to Savimbi the stand of the United States
government.
</P>
<P>
Landu Victor, congressman of the People's Democratic Party,
believed that the visit by Albright, a key figure in the U.S. who
is familiar with the Angolan peace process, will prove to be very
important to the development in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Victor said he hoped that "it is most important Albright will
meet with Savimbi during her visit in Angola."
</P>
<P>
Albright's seven-nation tour in Africa starting Monday
includes Ethiopia, Uganda, Rwanda, the Democratic Republic of
Congo, Angola, South Africa and Zimbabwe. 
