<HEADLINE> Lebanese New Opposition Bloc Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, December 9 (Xinhua) -- A new opposition bloc called
National Democracy Bloc (NDB) was established today in Lebanon
with the aim of reviving the country's political life and pushing
anti-sectarianism movement forward.
</P>
<P>
The bloc, comprising of three current and former parliament
members and other celebrities, was announced established by MP
Bayier Dakash at a news conference here.
</P>
<P>
Dakash stressed that the NDB is not a party, but a bloc aimed
at uniting all political and social powers.
</P>
<P>
He said that Lebanon is undergoing a very dangerous and
critical stage. "Democracy and freedom have become symbolic. The
gap between the authority and the people is widening," he added.
</P>
<P>
Dakash pointed out that the deteriorating economy has resulted
in an increased number of poor people, a high unemployment rate
and the rampancy of government officials' bribe and corruption.
</P>
<P>
He called on the people to join the non-sectarian bloc to
revive Lebanese political life and serve the people. 
</P>
