<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey's Court Attempts to Outlaw Islamic Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's Constitutional Court is
attempting to outlaw the pro-Islamic Welfare Party for its alleged
anti-secular nature, the Anatolia News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Rapporteur Yusuf Ozturk has prepared a report proposing the
Islamic party be disbanded according to either article 68 of the
Constitution or the the Law of Political Party, the news agency
said.
</P>
<P>
The report accuses the party of supporting Islamic
fundamentalists whose activities are aimed at undermining Turkey's
secular system.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the court Yekta Gungor Ozden has distributed the
report to the 11 judges of the court for final discussion.
</P>
<P>
According to Turkey's procedural law, the judges should meet
Wednesday, and the discussion could last seven to 10 days, which
might be extended when requested.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Welfare Party, headed by Turkey's former prime
minister Necmettin Erbakan, has long been attacked for its
sympathy and support for Islamic fundamentalism.
</P>
<P>
Last May, Chief Prosecutor Vural Savas filed with the
Constitutional Court a case demanding the closure of the party on
the grounds of its anti-secular activities.
</P>
<P>
Under Turkey's law of Political Party, Erbakan and senior
officials will be banned from political activities for at least
five years if their party is outlawed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971210.0062 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Plane Crash Kills Four in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 10 (Xinhua) -- A regional commuter plane
crashed in central Canada Tuesday, killing four people and
injuring 13 others, reports said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Three of the dead were killed in the crash, while a boy died
hours later in a Winnipeg hospital.
</P>
<P>
The plane crashed about 100 meters off the end of the runway at
about 3:30 p.m. local time while trying to land in "icy, misty"
weather.
</P>
<P>
There were two pilots and 15 passengers on board when the accident
happened.
</P>
<P>
Three of the survivors, two middle-aged men and a five-year old
boy, were critically injured.
</P>
<P>
The military sent a Hercules aircraft from Winnipeg, capital of
Manitoba province, to the crash site, a small Indian community called
Little Rapid Rapids, which is about 300 kilometers northeast of
Winnipeg.
</P>
<P>
But it couldn't land because the airstrip there was too small.
</P>
<P>
About five hours later, a small plane owned by the same
commuter company, managed to take off with the three seriously
injured aboard.
</P>
<P>
Yet, it was too late for the small boy, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The plane that crashed was an EMB 110, a twin-engine turb-prop
regional commuter with a capacity of 19 people. It was built in 1982
by Brazil.
</P>
<P>
The same kind of plane has crashed in Nigeria, Guatemala and
England. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
