<HEADLINE> France: Regret Over Serbs' Walkout From Conference in Bonn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 10 (Xinhua) -- France expressed its regret on
Wednesday over the Serbian delegation's walkout from an
international conference on Bosnia in Bonn.
</P>
<P>
The Serbs left in protest against mentioning the Kosovo issue
in the final text of the conference, regarding it as Western
interference in their internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
"Talking about the problem of Kosovo is not pointed against the
Serbs but aimed in the contrary at helping the Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia go out of its isolation," French Foreign Ministry
spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret said.
</P>
<P>
"It is not about representing any side but is about providing
help to the dialogue for finding a stable and long-term solution
(to the problem of Kosovo)," she added.
</P>
<P>
German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel and his French counterpart
Hubert Vedrine wrote to Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic at
the end of November, asking for a "special status" for Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The demand was categorically rejected by Yugoslavia. 
</P>
