<HEADLINE> ECOMOG Beefs up Sanctions on S. Leone Junta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The west African
peacekeeping force ECOMOG has stepped up its monitoring and
enforcement mechanism of the sanction and embargo imposed in July
by west African leaders against Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The west African leaders want constitutional rule to be
restored in Sierra Leone after the military overthrew the
civilian government on May 25.
</P>
<P>
According to ECOMOG officials based in Freetown, two fishing
vessels owned by a Ghanaian businesswoman operating in Sierra
Leone were seized on Monday by naval personnel of the Nigerian
ECOMOG warships on patrol on Sierra Leone waters.
</P>
<P>
"The vessels were escorted to the ECOMOG headquarters in
Monrovia," the officials said, without indicating what cargo the
vessels were carrying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Guinean ECOMOG Naval Contingent foiled an
attempt by four Sierra Leonean petrol dealers to smuggle 2,400
five-gallon containers of fuel by sea to Freetown.
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG sources in Jui, 13 miles east of Freetown said the
four men, "braved the terrific waves of the Atlantic Ocean early
Monday to smuggle the petrol on board a vessel equipped with two
outboard motor engines."
</P>
<P>
The arrested men were later released but the consignment of
petrol was seized.
</P>
<P>
In another development, as sanction and embargo intensified,
the state-run Sierra Leone News Agency reported today that the
prices of essential commodities have risen sharply in the last 72
hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
