<DOCNO> XIE19971210.0087 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-10 13:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Muslim Nations to Tap Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Islamic leaders are trying to
substantiate their religious identity with economic solidarity
among members of the Organization of the Islamic Conference
(OIC).
</P>
<P>
According to OIC Secretary General Azzeddine Laraki today,
OIC General Secretariat is preparing a four-year program aimed
at strengthening economic and commercial cooperation, which it
hopes will eventually lead to the formation of an Islamic common
market.
</P>
<P>
The 55 OIC member nations are at different economic
development levels, thus necessitating cooperation, trade and
exchange of information among them.
</P>
<P>
Laraki said the program will assess available capabilities,
determine implementation institutions and work out details based
on the principle of complementarity, mutual economic and
commercial interests and the spirit of Islamic independence.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, the richer and more capable countries will
assist poor ones, while cooperation in science, technology,
culture and communication will be carried out.
</P>
<P>
The OIC member states will also adjust their tariffs to
facilitate trade and cooperation toward concentrated and
concerted economic unity.
</P>
<P>
However, Lakari admitted that cultural differences of those
countries are posing a major obstacle to the realization of such
a goal and they should be carefully scrutinized and finally
resolved.
</P>
<P>
As to the financial problems of the OIC, he said a
comprehensive reform program has been drawn to collect more
funds, rationalize expenditures and streamline the administrative
system to cut deficit. But he did not elaborate.
</P>
<P>
The OIC has a small annual budget of about 10 million
U.S. dollars, far from being enough to carry out its missions in
the "best possible manner," and it is now ridden with a debt of
nearly 15 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971210.0088 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-10 </DATE_TIME>
