<HEADLINE> Iraqi Newspaper: OIC Summit Shows Failure of US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Arab and Islamic countries'
consensus on attending the Tehran summit intensively and at the
highest level indicates the failure of the U.S. policy in the
Middle East region, Iraqi newspaper Al-Jomhouriya said today.
</P>
<P>
The way these countries address the summit of the Organization
of the Islamic Conference (OIC) voices an American-Israeli sense
of failure and isolation as a result of the current Arab-Islamic
awakening, the official paper added.
</P>
<P>
The most significant U.S. reaction to the convention of the
Tehran summit is a statement by an American State Department
official asking the summit to avoid inciting against Israel and
attacking the Turkish-Israeli alliance, it noted..
</P>
<P>
The paper said that Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak
Mordechai's visit to Turkey which came one day before the Tehran
summit was intended to be another message of threat to the summit.
</P>
<P>
It called for setting up a comprehensive Islamic-Arab front to
stand against the U.S. evils.
</P>
<P>
The eighth OIC summit opened Tuesday in Iran's capital of
Tehran, with the participation of about 30 presidents,
vice-presidents, emirs and crown princes from 54 of OIC's 55
member states. The seat of Afghanistan is left vacant because the
OIC was divided as to who should represent the country.
</P>
<P>
The three-day summit commits itself to promoting "dignity,
dialogue and participation" in the Islamic world and is expected
to address a wide range of issues. 
</P>
