<HEADLINE> Exports of China's Zhejiang Province Surpass 10 Billion US Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 10 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang
Province exported products valued at some 10.1 billion US dollars
during the first 11 months of this year, thereby exceeding the
annual target by some 280 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time the province has recorded exports of 10
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang also led east China's provinces and municipalities in
export growth rate in the period .
</P>
<P>
The rise in exports resulted from local efforts to encourage the
development of foreign trade companies, enterprises with exporting
rights and foreign-funded businesses.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 641 foreign trade companies and 461
enterprises with exporting rights.
</P>
<P>
Finished industrial products accounted for 85.4 percent of the
local exports during the first eight months of this year, up 1.6
percentage points on the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The province has given priorities to the exportation of 100
varieties of product in order to improve the mix of exports.
</P>
<P>
Exports to the United States, the European Union, Africa and Latin
America have grown steadily. 
</P>
