<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Inflation Rate Up in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's inflation rate
based on consumer prices was 1.65 percent month-on-month due to an
increase in food costs, Trade and Industry Minister Tungky
Ariwibowo said today.
</P>
<P>
The November figure brought the January-November inflation to
9.01 percent year-on-year, Tungky Ariwibowo said after meeting
President Soeharto.
</P>
<P>
The main cause of the higher inflation in November was the rise
in the food price index, which reached 3.66 percent, he said.
</P>
<P>
The rise in the food price index contributed up to 78.8 percent
of the total inflation rate, he added.
</P>
<P>
To control prices, the government will supply the market with
adequate stocks of staple foods, he said.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's inflation rate last year was 6.46 percent, the
lowest in recent years. However, this year's inflation rate may
rise to a two-digit figure as a result of the current monetary
crisis and a long dry season which has caused crop production to
drop by more than 3 percent compared with last year, official
sources said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
