<HEADLINE> Exhibition Marks 60th Anniversary of Nanjing Massacre </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 10 (Xinhua) -- A painting and calligraphy
exhibition has opened recently in the Jiangsu Provincial Art
Gallery here, marking the 60th anniversary of the Nanjing Massacre.
</P>
<P>
The 125 works by domestic and overseas Chinese painters and
calligraphers artistically portray the historical event, which
took place over a half century ago.
</P>
<P>
Japanese aggressors invaded Shanghai on August 13, 1937, and
seized Nanjing, the Chinese capital at that time, on December 13.
</P>
<P>
Some 300,000 Chinese civilians and unarmed soldiers were
savagely butchered, and almost a third of the houses in the city
were destroyed by fire. 
</P>
