<HEADLINE> Chinese Province Boosts Farm Produce Processing Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 10 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province has been pushing its farm produce processing industry
into more markets in the country and the world.
</P>
<P>
So far, the province has penetrated more than 3,600 markets to
sell farm produces, with annual transactions exceeding 100 billion
yuan (12.5 billion U.S. dollars), local statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Annually, Guangdong's farm produce processing industry sells
3.4 million tons of fruit, 3.5 million tons of aquatic products,
2.8 million tons of meat and 13 million tons of vegetables. Many
of the products are exported.
</P>
<P>
With the increase in agricultural output, the provincial
government has decided to support 100 large-sized enterprises by
introducing overseas funds, technology and expertise.
</P>
<P>
The province also encourages the integration and annexation of
enterprises in the sector to raise the level of farm produce
processing and expand the production scale.
</P>
<P>
While raising its market share in the country, the province has
made efforts to develop international markets.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the province has helped farmers establish
organizations to improve their competitiveness in selling
agricultural products.  
</P>
</TEXT>
