<HEADLINE> China to Chair Next Session of Four-Party Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 10 (Xinhua) -- China will chair the next
plenary session of the four-party talks on the Korean Peninsula
scheduled in Geneva on March 16, 1998.
</P>
<P>
It was announced here on Wednesday at the end of the first
session of the four-party talks attended by delegations from
China, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), South
Korea and the United States.
</P>
<P>
As a result of a random draw conducted by the U.S., chairman of
the first session, the order of subsequent chairs was determined
to be China, South Korea, DPRK and the United States.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. will organize, before the second plenary session, an
ad hoc sub-committee for inter-sessional consultations in
mid-February in Beijing, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
It said the December 9-10 talks proceeded in a "cordial and
productive atmosphere." 
</P>
