<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sichuan Province of China Opens Wider to Outside World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The introduction of a series
of preferential polices has enabled southwest China's Sichuan
Province to achieve remarkable results in foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The province's foreign trade volume between January and October
hit 1.9 billion US dollars, up 9.3 percent on the 1996 same
period. Exports for the period surpassed 1.3 billion US dollars,
up 15.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Some 200 foreign-funded projects were approved during the 10-
month period, nearly doubling the figure for the 1996 same period. In
October alone, the province approved 32 foreign-funded projects,
with contracted investments standing at 578 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The province also contracted foreign projects valued at 347
million US dollars during the period.
</P>
<P>
Nine foreign financial organizations have established offices
in the capital city of Chengdu.
</P>
<P>
Related achievements have resulted from local efforts to
encourage exports and the establishment of group companies
involved in foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The province has also placed emphasis on the improving of the
local investment environment by issuing a series of favorable
polices and constructing a number of facilities for foreign
investors.
</P>
<P>
An increasing volume of foreign investment has been earmarked
for local basic industry, infrastructure construction, trade
companies, and the development of the stock exchange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
