<HEADLINE> UK's Oldest Woman Dies at 114 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Lucy Askew, Britain's oldest
woman, died on Tuesday at the age of 114.
</P>
<P>
Lucy, who had just celebrated her 114 birthday in September,
died peacefully in her sleep at a residential home in Loughton,
Essex, where she had lived out her last years.
</P>
<P>
Her local vicar, the Reverend David Broomfield, said Lucy, who
never married and had no children, had enjoyed relatively good
health until very recently.
</P>
<P>
She was described as a very gentle person of deep faith, and
her longevity has been attributed to her modest lifestyle.
</P>
<P>
Her brother died earlier this year aged 101.
</P>
<P>
The world's current oldest person is Louise Meilleur who is
116-year-old and lives now in Canada.  
</P>
</TEXT>
