<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Advises Local Government to Buy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni advised local government in the eastern district of
Mbale to buy mountainous areas to plant trees and avoid
disasters, "The Monitor" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The president told James Wapakhabulo, Ugandan parliament
Speaker on Sunday that he proposed Mbale district administration
to buy all the tops of the mountains in the district to plant
trees and evacuate local residents in the mountains to low lands
and thus avoid landslides.
</P>
<P>
The president was visiting Manjiya and Buwagogo counties where
floods caused by torrential rains in recent weeks damaged bridges
and hundreds of homes and imposed heavy life and property losses.
</P>
<P>
Rapidly expanding population forced local residents to settle
in all areas including swamps, mountains and river banks in the
east. 
