<HEADLINE> Beijing Reception Marks Anniversary of China-Australian Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's
Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC) hosted
a reception this evening, marking the 25th anniversary of the
establishment of diplomatic ties between China and Australia.
</P>
<P>
Chinese State Councillor Song Jian, visiting Australian Foreign
Minister Alexander Downer, and 100 Chinese and foreign dignitaries
attended the reception.
</P>
<P>
CPAFFC President Qi Huaiyuan proposed a toast and noted the
rising momentum and excellent development of 25 years of friendly
cooperative ties between the two countries in the political,
economic, trade, cultural, educational and scientific spheres.
</P>
<P>
Reciprocal high-level exchanges of visits have increased,
and friendship and contacts between the two peoples have been
strengthened in recent years, according to Qi.
</P>
<P>
Qi noted that the joint efforts of the governments and peoples
of China and Australia have forged a cooperative relationship
geared to the 21st century, with relations developing in a
sustained, stable and healthy manner.
</P>
<P>
The CPAFFC, China's major institution promoting
people-to-people friendship, will extend the greatest possible
effort to ensure fulfillment of related goals, said Qi.
</P>
<P>
Downer told guests attending the reception: "Today, Australia
and China can boast a mature relationship that is gaining new
momentum at all levels -- one that reflects the deep and expanding
involvement we both have in the life and work of the Asia
Pacific Region."
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that the relationship with China is "one of our
most important international relationships", which "will continue
to be based on the key principles of shared interests and mutual
respect".
</P>
<P>
Downer went on to say: "This 25th anniversary is a major
milestone", and "what we have achieved over the past 25 years --
and what lies in prospects for the next 25 (years) -- is cause for
considerable optimism."
</P>
<P>
"The Australian government will remain committed to building
and strengthening our relationship with China, and making its
undeniable potential a reality in the years ahead," said
Downer.
</P>
<P>
Song and Downer held joint discussions on issues of common
concern prior to the reception.
</P>
<P>
China and Australia established diplomatic ties on December 21,
1972, with bilateral relations having since entered a new period
of development.
</P>
<P>
China is Australia's fifth largest trade partner and export
market, as well as the major market for Australian wool. The 1996
trade volume between the two nations exceeded 5.1
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-one sister cities in the two nations have forged
friendly relations, with friendship organizations serving as
important conduits for promoting overall relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
