<HEADLINE> Charlton Player Sacked for Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 10 (Xinhua) -- English first division
Charlton's defender Jamie Stuart was sacked after testing positive
for cocaine and marijuana, a club official said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Manager Alan Curbishley said Charlton were terminating
Stuart's contract "to protect the good name of the club".
</P>
<P>
Stuart was tested at Charlton's training ground on November
17. The positive results was released by the Football Association
(F.A.) last Thursday and the following day he admitted taking the
substances.
</P>
<P>
Stuart is the fifth Charlton player to flunk a drugs test.
Teenager Jay Notley was allowed to resume his career with the club
last March after being suspended for four months for taking
cocaine, cannabis and ecstasy. 
