<HEADLINE> Australia's Attitude Towards China Appreciated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng expressed
appreciation over the Australian government's "friendly attitude"
towards China over the past year during a meeting with visiting
Australian Foreign Minister Alexander Downer here today.
</P>
<P>
"Australia has pursued the `One China' policy, supported Hong
Kong's smooth return to the motherland as well as China's early
entry to the WTO, and encouraged dialogues instead of
confrontation on the issue of human rights," Li said while
retrospecting bilateral relations in the past year.
</P>
<P>
China and Australia are both countries of great influence in
the Asia-Pacific region, and they share broad common interest and
shoulder common responsibility in safeguarding the world peace and
stability, especially in stimulating the regional economic
co-operation, the premier said.
</P>
<P>
He continued that China has always stressed its relations with
Australia and is ready to expand contacts, deepen understanding,
closer consultation, and develop co-operation between the two
countries through joint efforts in order to bring a developing
mutually beneficial Sino-Australian relations into the next
century.
</P>
<P>
Since the establishment of diplomatic relations 25 years ago,
bilateral co-operation in many sectors have undergone sound
progress, with economic and trade relations expanding and mutual
investment ever increasing, Li noted.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the new progress in Sino-Australian relations would
be impossible if it was without the efforts from Prime Minister
John Howard and Foreign Minister Downer himself, Li expressed the
belief that through concerted efforts of both sides, bilateral
relations will keep the present good momentum.
</P>
<P>
Downer agreed with Li on his evaluation on bilateral
relations. He spoke highly of the development of bilateral ties
especially the economic and trade relations over the past 25
years, saying that the Australian government and people are
pleased about the progress.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that China exerts a great influence and plays
an important role in the Asia-Pacific region and the even the
world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
The Australian government emphasizes relationship with China
and will adhere to the "One China" policy and continue to expand
its mutually-beneficial co-operation with China, Downer said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Li introduced to the Australian guests about China's
domestic situation. He also exchanged views with Downer on some
international and regional issues. 
</P>
