<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Customs Seizes 125g Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Customs seized 125
grams of cocaine on a foreign passenger at the Kai Tak Airport
Tuesday night, the Government Information Service reported today.
</P>
<P>
Customs officers intercepted the 27-year-old Zimbabwean man who
arrived in Hong Kong from Bangkok at 11 o'clock on Tuesday night,
finding 30 grams of cocaine in two pellets inside his shoes. He
discharged six more pellets of cocaine weighing 95 grams after he
was taken to hospital for examination.
</P>
<P>
It was the second time this year Customs officers at the
airport detected trafficking of cocaine by internal concealment.
The first case happened in September, when a Canadian man flying
in from South America was arrested for hiding 997 grams of cocaine
inside his body.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Customs and Excise Department has seized a total of
31.4 kg of cocaine so far this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
