<HEADLINE> Beijing Starts Work on "Second Chang'an Avenue" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Construction work on Ping'an
Avenue, dubbed the "second Chang'an Avenue", started in Beijing
today.
</P>
<P>
The 6,890-m. avenue runs parallel to Chang'an, from
Dongsishitiao Overpass on the eastern section of the Second Ring
Road to the Chegongzhuang Overpass on the western section of the
Second Ring Road. It is expected to cost two billion yuan (about
240 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
It will mean the demolition of 200,000 sq.m. of buildings. It
also traverses a dozen sites containing cultural relics that are
under state and provincial protection.
</P>
<P>
Deputy-Mayor Meng Xuenong described the project as being
significant for improving the traffic situation and promoting
local economic development.  
