<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philatelic Set For Year of Tiger Launched in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hong Kong, December 10 (Xinhua) -- A philatelic collection set
to celebrate the coming "Year of the Tiger" was Launched in Hong
Kong today.
</P>
<P>
The production of the set, which comprises one normal cover,
one set of postcards and one Souvenir Pack for limited
distribution, will tie-in with the new "Year of the Tiger" special
stamps to be issued by the Hong Kong Post on January 4 next year.
</P>
<P>
The launch of the philatelic collection set was announced by
the Agriculture and Fisheries Department (AFD) and the World Wide
Fund for Nature Hong Kong (WWF HK) here today.
</P>
<P>
The special First Day Cover and postcards present information
about the tiger, making them both educational and collectable.
</P>
<P>
David Melville, executive director of the WWF HK, said that
there are now only 5,000 tigers left due to human disturbance and
threat. "To save the tiger, it is essential that they be protected
from poaching and further loss of habitats," he said.
</P>
<P>
Frank Lau, assistant director of the AFD, said the tiger is one
of the most endangered species and attention should be paid to
protecting their habitat.  
</P>
</TEXT>
