<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Accelerate Urbanization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 10 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shanghai will
focus on developing special features in its drive to accelerate
urbanization of surrounding rural areas, according to local
sources.
</P>
<P>
Information from the municipal commission of agriculture said
that the city will construct its first 36 garden-like towns in the
city's rural areas in the forthcoming three years, where some
30,000 to 50,000 rural residents will live in high-rise buildings.
</P>
<P>
According to the information, competitions will be practiced to
select best designs for constructing these towns.
</P>
<P>
By the year 2000, urbanization rate of rural areas in Shanghai
will reach 45 percent, said the information.
</P>
<P>
Currently, 37.15 percent of Shanghai's rural areas have been
urbanized. In the urbanized areas, public facilities involving
highways, bridges, water and power supply have been constructed,
with industrial parks, residential quarters and agricultural zones
co-existing side by side. 
</P>
</TEXT>
