<HEADLINE> U.S. Secretary of State Visits Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 10 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright arrived here this morning for a two-day
official visit with an aim to enhance cooperation with Uganda and
discuss with Ugandan leaders the situation in the Great Lakes
region.
</P>
<P>
At a news briefing after his talks with Albright, Ugandan
President Yoweri Museveni said their talks focus on the bilateral
relations in the areas of investment and trade. They also
discussed African issues, he added.
</P>
<P>
Albright told the press that the United States is concerned
over the northern Gulu area where the anti-government forces are
fighting with the government army.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that Albright will go to Gulu this afternoon to
visit the World Vision rehabilitation centers and hospitals.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Secretary of State will leave here tomorrow for
Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
Uganda is the second leg of Albright's seven African nation
tour which has already brought her to Ethiopia and will also
take her to Rwanda, the Democratic epublic of Congo, Angola,
Zimbabwe and South Africa. 
