<HEADLINE> Eastern China Moving Traditional Industries To Western Parts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 10 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province
is planning on moving some of its traditional industries to
central and western parts of the country to improve its economic
structure.
</P>
<P>
The Changzhou Diesel Engine Group bought an otherwise bankrupt
factory in the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, and got a
considerable share of the market in the northwest China by using
its own technology, product quality, and management methods.
</P>
<P>
Then they made the same move in the Northeast and Southwest,
increasing annual output of a partner, the Changchun Diesel Engine
Group, in Jilin Province, from 700,000 to 1.5 million diesel
engines over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
The Little Swan Group in the city of Wuxi co-operated with the
Lotus Washing Machine Factory in Wuhan city of central China's
Hubei province, and increased its competitiveness in China's rural
market.
</P>
<P>
Labor-intensive enterprises in the province's pharmaceutical,
clothing and light industries have moved elsewhere in the country.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu has 3,731 cooperative projects in central and western
parts of the country, and in Shaanxi Province alone, it started
approximately 300 projects with a total investment of 600 million
yuan (72 million US dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
