<HEADLINE> Nigerian Engineers Urged to Copy Asian Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian engineers have been
asked to tap the ingenuity of their counterparts in the Asian
countries that would facilitate the development of a cheap and
sustained technology in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The search has become necessary now to escape "the quagmire of
underdevelopment," said Chief of General Staff Lt.-Gen. Oladipo
Diya, the number two person of Nigeria.
