<HEADLINE> Beijing Has ISDN Links with Ten Countries, Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 10 (Xinhua) -- ISDN (Integrated Services
Digital Network) services will be available between Beijing and
Britain, Macao and Finland later this month.
</P>
<P>
The service has linked Beijing with ten countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
As a modern telecommunications technique, the network enables
the transmission of data, as well as audio and video information
on one telecommunications line. Telephone conferences, remote
medical treatment and education can be held on the network.
</P>
<P>
Beijing first set up ISDN links with Japan and the United State
in 1996, and later with Germany, Singapore, Australia, the
Republic of Korea, Switzerland, Hong Kong and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has opened ISDN services to big Chinese cities of
Shanghai, Guangzhou and Nanjing.  
</P>
