<HEADLINE> Experts Choose China's "Famous Snacks" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The China Cuisine Association
(CCA) has awarded the title "Famous Chinese Snack" to 396 types of
food from around the country.
</P>
<P>
Experts from 29 Chinese provinces, municipalities, and
autonomous regions met in Hangzhou from December 5 to 7 to select
the winners.
</P>
<P>
These snacks included Guangdong's Chashaobao (a sweet steamed
pork-filled bun), Tianjin's Goubuli (another type of steamed
pork-filled bun), Beijing's Douzhi (a drink made from beans), and
Sichuan's Lai Family Tangyuan (a soup with stuffed dumplings made
from glutinous rice flour), as well as 54 varieties of Muslim food.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Shirao, the CCA's president, said that these Chinese
snacks represent part of the country's heritage and its culture of
cuisine, and are popular for their rich variety, low cost, and
delicious taste. 
