<HEADLINE> Drug Education Video Being Shown To Chinese Youth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Video tapes are being
distributed among China's schools, from primary to college, as
part of the war on drugs.
</P>
<P>
The series of videaos, "We Reject Drugs", was produced by the
Higher Learning Press, with the help of the National Narcotics
Control Committee and the State Education Commission.
</P>
<P>
The number of youngsters using drugs is on the rise in China,
where drug-related crimes are becoming a big problem, according to
today's Guangming Daily.
</P>
<P>
Police departments report that the number of cases involving
drug abuse among the young now account for 80 percent of the total
number of reported cases, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The National Narcotics Control Committee and the State
Education Commission have jointly issued a circular that urge
education departments to publicize anti-drug policies and to teach
students to "love life and stay away from drugs".
</P>
<P>
The four-part series of videos covers general information about
drugs, the hazards of drug abuse, how to avoid using drugs, and the
criminal aspects of drug abuse and trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The tape has been warmly received by teachers and students at
schools where it has been shown. 
</P>
