<HEADLINE> Tibet Hit By Snowstorms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Nagqu Prefecture in China's
Tibet Autonomous Region has had heavy snowfall this winter that
has blocked roads and made life difficult for local people.
</P>
<P>
Highways have been covered with thick ice and the snowfall in
the central part of the prefecture was 30 to 50 cm on
average. Some villages reported nearly a meter of snowfall.
</P>
<P>
The prefectural government reported snow falling 30 times, on
63.7 percent of the prefecture, from mid-September to the end of
November. The previous record snowstorm was 12 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The heavy snow has caused problems for herdsmen and loss of
weight for their livestock. It is reported that some herdsmen have
to use their furniture for fuel.
</P>
<P>
The regional government has brought in 400,000 yuan (about
48,000 US dollars) worth of fuel and food to disaster-stricken
areas, and local officials say the amount of stored grain can last
until spring.  
</P>
</TEXT>
