<DOCNO> XIE19971210.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Spreads Efficient Irrigation in Farming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 10 (Xinhua) -- China has been spreading
water-efficient irrigation in farming in its vast rural areas by
constructing water-saving projects and application of advanced
water-saving technology.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhang Chunyuan, Vice Minister of Water Resources,
who was here attending a national meeting on water-efficient
irrigation, China has invested 11 billion yuan in water-saving
irrigation projects in farming since the beginning of 1996 and has
completed construction of water-efficient irrigation facilities of
various kinds on 2.33 million hectares of farmland.
</P>
<P>
It has also established 70 high-standard water-efficient
irrigation demonstration parks, said the vice minister.
</P>
<P>
China is one of the world's 13 water-poor countries and its per
capita water resource availability is just one quarter of the
world's average level. Water shortages have become a key factor
in restricting agricultural development.
</P>
<P>
China started to spread water-efficient irrigation technology
nationwide in 1996. It has designated 300 major counties to pilot
increasing grain output through water-efficienct farming, as well
as a group of water-saving irrigation zones.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two years, many provincies and autonomous regions
of the country have set up leading groups to take charge of the
effort. Great progress has been made in the development of
water-efficient irrigation.
</P>
<P>
Central and local governments have also taken effective
measures to arouse the initiatives of localities and individual
farmers in making investment on water-efficient irrigation in
farming.
</P>
<P>
The spreading of water-efficient irrigation has greatly helped
increase agricultural output. In the past two years, an
additional 19 billion kg of grain have been gathered. 
</P>
