<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Improving Its Old City Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Now that Shanghai's
Fuxingdonglu Road is open to traffic, the massive renewal project
in the old Nanshi part of the city is partially completed.
</P>
<P>
The 2.2-km road runs through the hub of the city and an area
that contain shacks, and unsafe housing that need to be upgraded,
with an average width of less than 12 meters.
</P>
<P>
The renewal project, which began in March of last year and cost
1.5 billion yuan (180 million U.S. dollars), which mainly came
from the city government, meant moving 5,690 households and 282
units.
</P>
<P>
The average width of the six-lane new road is 45 meters. It
also has 30,000 sq.m. of greenery alongside.
</P>
<P>
Residential and commercial buildings are also being built with
Hong Kong and Singapore financial backing.
</P>
<P>
Shun Weiguo, head of the Nanshi District, says that by the next
century a 121 ha. landscape of improved residential buildings will
be built in the central part of the city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
