<DOCNO> XIE19971210.0174 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Surges in East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Suzhou City of east China's
Jiangsu Province did 7.04 billion U.S. dollars worth of foreign
trade in the first ten months this year.
</P>
<P>
The figure is 740 million U.S. dollars more than the city's
total foreign trade volume of the entire year of 1996, said local
sources.
</P>
<P>
Local officials attributed the rapid growth in foreign trade to
their efforts made to improve the city's export-oriented economic
structure, foster new economic powerhouses, and bring about a
simultaneous growth of foreign trade scale and efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The city has approved the establishment of 7,485
overseas-financed businesses, 5,112 of which have already started
operation.
</P>
<P>
Suzhou, dubbed as "paradise on earth" and famed for its
numerous stylish parks, has treated overseas-backed enterprises as
a powerhouse to develop export-oriented economy, and has worked
out preferential policies to encourage them to increase exports.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the overseas-financed enterprises
in the city had exported 2.86 billion U.S. dollars worth of
commodities by the end of October this year, up 49.7 percent and
accounting for 69.6 percent of Suzhou City's total.
</P>
<P>
The city has also made efforts to adjust its export structure
and to concentrate on development and export of high- and
new-technology products. Economic benefits of export enterprises
have been improving as export scale increases and the structure of
export commodities improves.
</P>
<P>
Suzhou has also made great efforts to expand overseas markets
since the beginning of this year. Now commodities made in the city
are exported to 111 countries and regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
