<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
decline on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index lost another 30.7 points to close at 1,703.52
points today.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that prices fell lower because of worries over
Indonesian President Soeharto's health and the overnight weakness
on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank further to 149.02 million units,
valued at 340.58 million Singapore dollars (210.23 million US
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 194 to 90, while 326
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Technologies Engineering again was the most
actively traded stock as it registered a turnover of 23.04 million
units. It was followed by Genting which had 6.78 million shares
traded. IPC Corporation was next with 4.33 million shares changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
Uniphoenix led the gainers of the day as it rose by 30 cents to
finish at 3.6 Singapore dollars. KL Kepong increased by 18 cents
to end at 3.84 Singapore dollars, while Roth S. picked up by 15
cents to close at 8.9 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Genting was the biggest loser as it declined
by 2.09 dollars to end at 0.2 US dollar. Local soft drink and food
maker F&AMP;N fell by 50 cents to close at 9.15 Singapore dollars.
Property developer City Developments lost 45 cents to finish at
8.1 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
