<HEADLINE> China Building Radial Level Oil Well By High-Pressure Water Flow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese oilfield experts and
engineering workers have successfully constructed its first radial
level oil channel in northeast China's Liaohe Oilfield by using
high-pressure water flows.
</P>
<P>
Information reaching here said that in early November, experts
and workers used high-pressure water flows to cut a 15.86 m-long
passage, with a diameter of 110-130 meters, from the
1,013. 2-m-deep oil-bearing strata of an existing well.
</P>
<P>
The underground situation of the Liaohe Oilfield is very
complicated. After certain periods of development, the use of
conventional methods to exploit oil in some wells have been proved
to be difficult and bear low economic efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The application of radial horizontal well drilling technology
can help raise the oil recovering rate and explorable reserves by
big margins, tap production potentials of the old oilfield to the
greatest extent, improve service life and production capacity of
oil wells, said experts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
