<HEADLINE> China Issues Stamps on Telecom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Posts and
Telecommunications announced today the issuance of a set of
special China's Telecommunications stamps, the first on the
achievements of the country's public telephone network.
</P>
<P>
The set of four stamps, 30-by-40 millimeters in size, features
digital transmission, program-controlled exchange, data
telecommunications and mobile telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
According to a senior official of the Ministry of Posts and
Telecommunications at today's ceremony, a multi-dimensional
digital transmission network has been formed with
optical cable, satellites and digital microwave.
</P>
<P>
China's public telephone network is now the second largest in
the world, with a total capacity of 104 million lines. The
capacity is projected to reach 170 million lines at the end of the
century.
</P>
<P>
The data telecommunications networks have basically covered the
whole country. The capacity of China's mobile phone network now
ranks third in the world.  
</P>
