<HEADLINE> Human Rights Day Observed in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The Human Rights Day was
observed in Bangladesh today with its leaders reaffirming the
country's commitments to the principles proclaimed in the
Universal Declaration of Human Rights.
</P>
<P>
Bangladeshi President Shahabuddin Ahmed said in a message that
Bangladesh is observing the day this year with a note of higher
optimism inspired by the progress in the field of human rights
despite the constraints of a least developed country.
</P>
<P>
In a message issued on the eve of the day, Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina reaffirmed Bangladesh's deep commitment to the
rights of every human individual and the principles enunciated in
the Universal Declaration of Human Rights.
</P>
<P>
"Our solemn pledge on this occasion will be to translate those
ideals for every citizen of Bangladesh and to strive to secure
those rights for the whole mankind," she said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Ministry of Law, Justice and Parliament Affairs
and different organizations also held various kinds of activities
in Dhaka to mark the day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
