<HEADLINE> 4 Injured as Philippine Military Chopper Crash-lands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 10 (Xinhua) -- A Philippine air force
helicopter crash-landed today on a former American air force bomb
target training range in the Northern Philippines, injuring four
of the six soldiers on board, a military report said.
</P>
<P>
The report by the military authorities said that the helicopter
was on a training flight from Villamor Air Base in Manila to the
former U.S. air base at Clark Field in Central Luzon when it
developed mechanical trouble over Upper Crow Valley, Tarlac, the
Northern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter was forced to land on Crow Valley, known as a
bomb dropping point of American fighters and bombers, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
The injured were rushed to a nearby hospital, it said.
</P>
</TEXT>
