<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sichuan Provides Good Service to Foreign Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan Province in southwest
China has taken measures to protect the rights and interest of
overseas investors, and its sincerity in the effort is paying off.
</P>
<P>
Not long ago, a foreign investor showed interest in an
expressway project of the province. But the province's Party
Secretary Xie Shijie told him frankly that though the highway
would have huge amounts of traffic flow upon completion, it
couldn't bring good benefits as most of the traffic flow would be
free of charge.
</P>
<P>
Instead, Xie encouraged the investor to shift his capital to
hydropower development, which would bring steady returns. The
investor followed his advice.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan has adopted an investment policy of "You get good
profits and we enjoy fast development". Accordingly, such
multinational corporations as Motorola, Siemens, Bell, and Toyota
began to invest in the province. By the first half of this year,
the province had opened more than 4,600 overseas-backed businesses
</P>
<P>
The Parkson Plaza, a joint venture, complained about excessive
consulting service charges. The provincial government intervened
and ordered the departments concerned to apologize to the company
and return the money.
</P>
<P>
The province set up a foreign investor complaints center last
year to take care of complaints by overseas-funded enterprises. By
now the center has received more than 100 complaint cases, most of
which have been dealt with satisfactorily. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
