<HEADLINE> Private Economy Encouraged in North China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Shanxi Province in north China
will take steps to further promote the private sector as it has
become a major factor behind local economic growth, said Hu Fuguo,
the province's Party Secretary.
</P>
<P>
He made this remark during a recent meeting with private
entrepreneurs. The majority of the private business people have
made a career through hard work under market competition, and made
considerable contributions to the society and the public, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We will work out plans and policies to further develop the
private sector in the form of cooperation, acquisition, leasing,
and joint stock. Fine private entrepreneurs can also compete to
become managers of state enterprises," the official said.
</P>
<P>
"So long as the private sector does business abiding by the
law, we will give it a free hand in development," he added.
</P>
<P>
Statistics showed that by the end of last year the province's
private sector had had 13.5 billion yuan in registered capital,
accounting for 9.49 percent of the province's total, involving 1.4
million employees.
</P>
<P>
The province will also make a new effort to help form some
private enterprise groups and develop name-brand products.
</P>
</TEXT>
