<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji Hails Sino-Australian Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu
Rongji said here today that China appreciates the friendly stance
of the Australian government on some major issues during the past
year.
</P>
<P>
Sino-Australian relations, which started a long time ago, have
steadily advanced, Zhu said, adding that momentum has developed
recently in bilateral ties, with a remarkable growth of
cooperation in various fields.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks during a meeting with visiting Australian
Foreign Minister Alexander Downer.
</P>
<P>
Zhu went on to say that Downer could personally experience the
friendly feelings of the Chinese people toward their Australian
counterparts through his current China trip, which takes place on
the 25th anniversary of the establishment of Sino-Australian ties.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier recalled his Australian visit last May, during
which he and Downer reached consensus on a wide range of issues,
including bilateral ties and other problems of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Downer said that the 25th anniversary of Australia-China
diplomatic relations is a joyful event and worth celebrating. The
Australian government speaks highly of the achievements in the two
countries' ties over the past 25 years and is satisfied with the
current development of bilateral relations, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Australian government values its ties with China and is
ready to work with China to further advance bilateral ties in an
all-round manner, he said.
</P>
<P>
The two officials also exchanged views on issues concerning
regional and international issues during the meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
