<DOCNO> XIE19971210.0203 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai ATMs Connected With Citywide Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 10 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,600 ATMs in
Shanghai have successfully been connected with an electronic
network, accounting for 98 percent of the city's automated teller
machines.
</P>
<P>
Nine financial institutions have issued 5.24 million savings
cards and 1.47 million credit cards, according to sources from the
local branch of the People's Bank of China, the central bank.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that daily ATM business transactions average 14
million yuan (1.75 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Shanghai also has made progress in computerizing bank account
settlements on 3,668 point-of-sale machines.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has been attempting to tap the international market by
hooking up ATMs with the Visa International network.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, Visa card holders worldwide can
draw cash directly from 518 ATMs in the city. Visa International
is the world's largest issuer of credit cards, with 700 million
cardholders.
</P>
<P>
Sources said the city is attempting to link ATMs with another
international network. 
</P>
</TEXT>
