<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anhui Successful in Reducing Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The number of people who live
under the poverty line in east China's Anhui Province has dropped
by 60 percent from 4.18 million in 1993 to the present 1.6
million, a provincial official announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Most of the poor people used to live in the Dabie Mountainous
area, southern Anhui and flood-afflicted areas along both banks of
the Huaihe River.
</P>
<P>
The official attributed the success to improvement of farming
infrastructures, especially the construction of water conservancy
facilities in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Central and local governments have allocated three billion yuan
to build flood-control projects which can prevent 2.28 million ha
of farmland from flood damage, repair 1,500 roads with a total
length of 110,000 km and erect 4,800 drinking water projects.
</P>
<P>
In addition, nine central government departments including the
State Planning Commission have sent experts and officials down to
poverty-stricken counties to offer technological guidance, funding
and information. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971210.0205 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Cape Verde Defense Ministers Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian held talks here today with his Cape Verde counterpart,
Ulpio Fernandes.
</P>
<P>
Chi, who is also vice-chairman of the Chinese Central Military
Commission and State Councillor, said that despite being separated
by an ocean, China and Cape Verde share a tradition of friendship.
</P>
<P>
Recent years have seen fruitful bilateral cooperation in
political, economic and cultural areas, he said, adding that the
armed forces of the two countries have also maintained close
exchanges and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Chi said he is convinced that Fernandes' visit will help deepen
mutual understanding and boost the existing friendly cooperative
relations between the two nations and their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his appreciations to the Cape Verde government for
its contribution to safeguarding peace and stability in Africa and
the world.
</P>
<P>
He also thanked the government for its "one China" position and
its support to China on human rights issues.
</P>
<P>
Fernandes, who is the first Cape Verde defense minister to
visit China, said China is a great friend of his country.
</P>
<P>
Cape Verde's cooperative partnership with China is of great
significance to economic development in western Africa and the
continent's peace and stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Fernandes said he hopes that the two countries can
expand bilateral cooperation in various areas, and that the Cape
Verde government will adhere to the "one China" stand and continue
to support China's reunification.
</P>
<P>
Qian Shugen, deputy chief of the general staff of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army, attended the talks.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Chi presided over a welcoming ceremony for
Fernandes, who arrived here Tuesday for an official and goodwill
visit at the invitation of Chi.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
