<HEADLINE> Turkey's Population Reaches 62 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's population is
estimated at around 62 million, the Anatolia News Agency today
quoted the results of a recent census as saying.
</P>
<P>
The census, which was conducted throughout the country on
November 30, shows that 40 million people live in urban areas,
accounting for 65.4 percent of the total population.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's population increased by 10.7 percent over the last
seven years compared with 56 million provided by the 1990 census.
</P>
<P>
Experts, however, noted that the country's population growth
rate has decreased to 1.4 percent from 2.1 percent seven years
ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
