<HEADLINE> Speaking Trashcans On Beijing Streets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Try to put your plastic bag in
a green trashcan on the streets of Beijing and you're liable to
find it telling you, "Please put only paper waste in", but a
yellow one will tell you, "Thanks for helping protect the
environment."
</P>
<P>
The colored talking trashcans are made by the city's
environmental protection department and can be found in front of
large department stores. They tell people to separate their trash
and to put it into the proper can: green for paper, blue for metal
and glass, yellow for plastic, and red for other items.
</P>
<P>
The city of 12 million produces a large amount of trash every
day, including 600,000 styrofoam food boxes. When trash is
discarded indiscriminately, it results in serious pollution and
wastes resources.
</P>
<P>
An environmental protection department official says that after
the trash is separated, it is transported to disposal plants where
it can be recycled. More of these trashcans will be used in
future, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
