<HEADLINE> China Building Electron Gun Components Production Base in Dalian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The State Planning Commission
has recently decided to invest 197 million yuan in constructing a
base for producing electron gun components for color picture tubes
in Dalian, a port city of northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The Dalian Color Picture Tube Co. Ltd. imported key technology
and equipment for production of electron gun components for color
picture tubes from Toshiba Company of Japan in 1990 and has formed
a capacity of independently developing a 64-cm electron gun
component for color picture tubes.
</P>
<P>
The Dalian company, designated as the only base for producing
electron gun components for color picture tubes in China, now
holds 40 percent of the market share in China, according to local
sources.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that besides importing a small amount of key
equipment and die sets, the company will mainly use existing
equipment and technology to carry out new product development
independently.
</P>
<P>
It has already had a registered capital of 59.9 million yuan
for construction of the production base of electron gun components
for color picture tubes.
</P>
<P>
By the year of 2001, it is expected to be able to produce 47.8
million sets of electron gun components for color picture tubes in
a great varieties ranging from 47 cm to 74 cm, and will also earn
1.5 billion yuan from sales of such products, as well as increase
its market share to over 60 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
