<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel will pay a two-day state visit to Pakistan from December
18-19 to enhance friendly relations between the two countries,
foreign office sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Pakistan, Demirel will meet acting President
Wasim Sajjad and Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif to discuss bilateral
and regional issues, the sources said.
</P>
