</P>
<P>
-- South African weather experts Tuesday criticized a local
newspaper report that the El Nino weather pattern had been
weakened and no longer posted a threat. They said the phenomenon
varied in intensity from month to month but was on course to
unleash a very hot and dry summer over southern Africa.
</P>
