Sowetan
</P>
<P>
-- The South African government spent 167 billion Rand (34.8
billion U.S. Dollars) in the 1995/96 financial year, about 13.5
percent higher than the previous financial year, the Central
Statistics Service said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Business Day
</P>
<P>
-- South Africa's Producer inflation tumbled to 4.9 percent in
October from 6.1 percent in September, sparkling bullish
sentiment on further interest rate cuts as economists hastened to
change their inflation forecasts.
