<TEXT>
<P>
Ho Chi Minh, Vietnam, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan,
Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party (CPC) Central Committee, left here today for New
Zealand, winding up his four-day goodwill visit to Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
While leaving the city, Li sent a telegram to the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV) to express his
thanks for the cordial and friendly reception.
</P>
<P>
