<DOCNO> XIE19971210.0233 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda Coffee Export Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Uganda coffee export dropped
60 percent in October and November but the overall export project
of the crop this season will not be affected, The New Vision
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Uganda exported 130,828 bags in October and 179,600 bags in
November this year, comparing to their counterparts of 340,000
bags and 436,000 bags a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Every bag contains 60 kilogram of coffee.
</P>
<P>
Uganda Coffee Development Authority attributed the sharp drop
to the heavy rains recent weeks delaying the drying of coffee
seeds countrywide, and the coffee season will end around April
instead of the usual February, said William Naggaga, the
Secretary of Uganda Coffee Board.
</P>
<P>
But he assured the overall coffee export project will not be
affected.
</P>
<P>
Coffee is a leading export plant that earns some 65 percent of
its foreign currency.
</P>
<P>
Uganda has exported a record of 4.2 million bags of coffee in
last coffee season.
</P>
<P>
Ugandan officials predicted the country will export some 4
million bags of coffee this season. The shortfall of 200,000 bags
is caused by drought earlier this year, they explained.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
