<HEADLINE> Security Guards Rob Bank in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Three security guards today
robbed the bank they should protect in Makati City, Metro Manila
and escaped with a big loot, police said today.
</P>
<P>
The Makati City police had dispatched two investigation teams
to get the suspects, police said. They did not reveal how much
money was taken away by the robbers.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigation showed that the robbery took place at
about 7 a.m. when two female tellers arrived at the Malayan Bank
in Legazpi Village, Makati City. The suspects tied up the tellers
and looted the bank's vault.  
</P>
</TEXT>
