<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Active in Technology Exchanges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has been active in
technological exchanges, according to today's overseas edition of
"People's Daily."
</P>
<P>
Statistics for the past 10 years show that the city attracted
more than 10 billion yuan (1.25 billion U.S. dollars) in
contracted volume, accounting for one-tenth of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai technology markets have provided more than 10,000
technologies for local industrial enterprises since the 1990s.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Technology Exchange Center has recorded a transaction
volume of 5,082 technologies, involving 2.556 billion yuan (307
million U.S. dollars) since it went into operation three years ago.
</P>
<P>
A technology market fund has also been established together
with a technology information data base.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the city exported six technologies to the United
States and Japan, earning more than 28 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
