<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Airport Provides Better Service to Passengers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's Hongqiao Airport
has introduced new regulations to protect the convenience of
passengers who miss plane due to bad weather or traffic jams.
</P>
<P>
Convenience will also be offered to those who badly need air
tickets in emergency.
</P>
<P>
According to regulations of the Civil Aviation Administration
of China, the handling of boarding formalities should be completed
30 minutes prior to the taking-off time.
</P>
<P>
In order to help passengers in emergency, the Hongqiao Airport
began to offer a 10 minute grace to those who miss the stipulated
dead line and help them onto the earliest plane possible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
