<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Agricultural Breakthrough Reported in Ningxia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The total industrial output
of township enterprises processing agricultural and farm-related
products is expected to reach 9 billion yuan (1.1 billion
U.S. dollars) in northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region
this year.
</P>
<P>
That is an increase of 26.5 percent over 1996 in the sector and
amounts to 70 percent of the total rural product in the region,
according to local statistics.
</P>
<P>
The region's grain output topped 2.5 billion kilograms this
year despite a number of natural disasters. The output of meat,
eggs and milk all increased by 30-to-50 percent.
</P>
<P>
These achievements in agricultural production have led to
improvements in living conditions. More than 600,000 local farmers
are leading comparatively well-off lives. Another 200,000 farmers
in the southern mountainous areas have risen above the poverty
line. Per capita net income in the rural areas has hit 1,580 yuan
(198 U.S. dollars), 6 percent more than 1996.
</P>
<P>
The government's investment in agriculture increased 22 percent
over last year, said Cui Yongqing, director of the region's
Agricultural Department.
</P>
<P>
Since last year the region has transformed 43,000 hectares of
medium- and low-yield fields into high-yield land, and improved
some 70,000 hectares of irrigated areas. The region also has added
37,000 hectares of farmland.
</P>
<P>
Cui said that the total grain-growing areas exceed 770,000
hectares, an all-time high, and that more than 50 percent of farm
products are sold in the markets.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the region has adopted advanced technologies to
guide agricultural production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
