<HEADLINE> Beijing Fulfills Customs Tax Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The customs office of the
Chinese capital collected 4.73 billion yuan (about 600 million
U.S. dollars) in taxes by Dec. 3, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
The customs office fulfilled its yearly tax-revenue target, 4.7
billion yuan, 28 days ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
The improved collection of duties came mainly as a result of
greater importance attached to the import tax, greater publicity
of customs law and continued reforms, according to a Beijing
official.
</P>
<P>
Another reason for the smooth collection was an increased
effort to avoid tax losses. For instance, 75.4 million yuan in
customs taxes was recovered because many items had been
undervalued.  
</P>
