<HEADLINE> Campaign Seeks to Attract Winter Visitors to Mount Huangshan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 10 (Xinhua) -- A promotion campaign has
been launched to attract Guangdong residents to scenic Mount
Huangshan as a winter destination.
</P>
<P>
Huangshan in east China's Anhui Province is considered by many
to be the most beautiful mountain in the country, who say: "After
visiting Huangshan, you may not be interested in any other
mountain in China."
</P>
<P>
The mountain is on the United Nations Educational, Scientific
and Cultural Organization's list of World Natural and Cultural
Heritage sites.
</P>
<P>
Though most tourists visit the mountain during the peak season
between May and October, its beauty in winter makes it equally
attractive.
</P>
<P>
Since winter tours were introduced in 1991, more than 600,000
Chinese and overseas tourists have visited the mountain in the
off-season. Between January and November, tourist arrivals
increased by 32 percent.
</P>
<P>
As one of the richest regions in the country, the Pearl River
Delta area centering around Guangzhou has also been China's major
tourism market. Increasingly, area residents are choosing to go to
the northern part of the country for the snowy landscapes.
</P>
<P>
According to Yang Liwei, vice mayor of the city of Huangshan,
all major air routes will continue to operate in winter, and all
the scenic spots on the mountain will remain open.
</P>
<P>
Through March 15, Huangshan's hotel rates will be reduced 30 to
50 percent and entry fees will be lowered for scenic spots.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
