<HEADLINE> Chongqing Strengthens Evaluation of Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The Chongqing Import and
Export Commodity Inspection Bureau has discovered a difference of
120 million yuan (15 million U.S. dollars) between the value
quoted for equipment provided by overseas partners in joint
ventures and the equipment's actual value.
</P>
<P>
The bureau has evaluated 183 groups of equipment and
installations since 1993. The quoted price for the equipment
provided by overseas investors was more than 980 million yuan
(122.5 million U.S. dollars). However, the bureau's evaluation
established the actual value at 860 million yuan (107.5 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The overseas partners will be required to compensate Chongqing
for the 120-million-yuan difference, according to the bureau.
</P>
<P>
When importing equipment, some overseas investors reportedly
quote higher prices than the actual worth. For example, a chemical
plant in Chongqing put up 600,000 U.S. dollars while foreign
investors offered 790,000 U.S. dollars to buy equipment for a
joint venture.
</P>
<P>
The foreign investors were asked to use the 1.39 million
dollars to buy the equipment. However, the equipment was evaluated
at only 360,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The evaluation of overseas investment serves as an important
economic safeguard, said Zhong Dechang, director of the bureau,
and should help the city become the economic center for the upper
reaches of the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, the city approved 134
overseas-funded projects, an increase of 14 percent over the same
period last year. The projects involve contractual capital of 195
million U.S. dollars, up 13 percent; and 106 million U.S. dollars
have actually been spent, up 25 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
