right for a six-game shootout with FIDE champion Anatoly Karpov of
Rissia in Lausanne of Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Indian Viswanathan Anand is a favorite to challenge Karpov for
the top prize Money of 1,370,000 U.S. dollars, since the rival
Professional Chess Association World Champion Garry Kasparov and
Vladimir Kramnik were absent from the FIDE field. 
