<HEADLINE> Inter To Chase Title, Villa Makes Quarterfinals Debut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Inter had heat on the defending
champion Schalke after advancing into the UEFA Cup Quarterfinals
on a 3-2 aggregate with a 3-0 win over Strasbourg, and Aston Villa
made its quarterfinal debut in the competition in 20 years.
</P>
<P>
Inter sensation Ronaldo opened the scoring on a free kick in
the 28th minute, Argentine midfielder Javier Zanetti evened the
aggregate in the 49th and another Argentine, Diego Simeone, scored
the winning goal with 17 minutes remaining.
</P>
<P>
The reigning champion Schalke joined Inter in the final eight
by beating a 10-men Sporting Braga of Portugal 2-0.
</P>
<P>
Martin Max and Rene Eijkelkamp scored in the second half as
Schalke advanced 2-0 on aggregate following a scoreless tie in the
first leg of the third-round tie in Braga two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
In Birmingham, England, Aston Villa rallied from a 2-1 deficit
to beat Steaua Bucharest 2-0 to reach the UEFA Cup quarterfinals
for the first time since 1978.
</P>
<P>
In Moscow, Spartak's striker Alexander Shirko scored in
overtime to hand Karlsruhe a 1-0 loss, sending the Moscow club
into the quarterfinals on a 1-0 aggregate.
</P>
<P>
Lazio of Rome edged out visiting Rapid Vienna 1-0 to advance on
a 3-0 aggregate. In France, Auxerre advanced on a 3-0 aggregate
after beating FC Twente of the Netherlands 1-0 in the first leg.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, VfL Bochum will entertain Ajax after the
Germany club enjoyed a 4-2 lead in the first leg. 
</P>
</TEXT>
