<HEADLINE> New Investment Focus in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Fuyang in east China's
Anhui Province, the major hub of the Beijing-Kowloon Railway,
anticipates an increasing influx of foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
The Fuyang Section of the Beijing-Kowloon Railway, which runs
192 kilometers and has 13 stations, makes the city one of the
nation's six major railway hubs.
</P>
<P>
Marshalling yards at Fuyang's railway stations lead Asia with a
capacity of 10,000 train units annually.
</P>
<P>
Convenient transportation provided by the railway is expected
to greatly enhance local economic development.
</P>
<P>
The central government has invested over 20 billion yuan in a
number of key projects in the city in recent years, with the
wide-ranging projects covering the railway, highway, airport,
power generation, animal husbandry, and agricultural sectors.
</P>
<P>
Since 1995, the city has attracted more than 300 overseas
investors from a number of countries and regions, including Japan,
the United States, Singapore, Thailand, and Australia. Total
foreign investment stands at 10 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Fuyang Power Plant, which has introduced 500 million US
dollars in foreign investment, is the largest overseas-funded
project in the province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
