<HEADLINE> Poland, Moldova to Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Economic and cultural
cooperation has a special position in Polish-Moldovan relations,
said Visiting Polish President Aleksander Kwasniewski Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Kwasniewski, who arrived in Moldova Tuesday for a two-day
formal visit, made the remark after meeting with his Moldovan
counterpart Peter Luchinsky, according to reports from Chisinau.
</P>
<P>
Poland hopes to expand its cooperation with Moldova, especially
in the fields of trade and transport. This kind of cooperation
will help the two countries establish links in the Baltic and
Black Sea region, said Kwasniewski.
</P>
<P>
The president also promised that Poland will spare no efforts
to seek a peaceful settlement to disputes in riparian regions
along the Dnestr River. The country will also provide aid to
Moldova's political and economic reforms.
</P>
<P>
The trade and economic cooperation between Poland and Moldova
has gained remarkable growth recently. The trading volume of
the first nine months this year reached 11.6 million U.S. dollars,
up 50 percent compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Moldova mainly exports vegetable oil, textiles and chemical
products to Poland. The country imports steel, tobacco and
medicine from Poland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
