<HEADLINE> Italy Backs European Aerospace Restructuring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Italian Premier Romano Prodi is
"extremely interested" in proposals for the reorganisation of the
European aerospace and defence electronics industry, and fully
approves the reorganisation of Airbus, said a government statement
issued here today.
</P>
<P>
The proposals were contained in today's joint declaration by
German Chancellor Helmut Kohl, French President Jacques Chirac and
British Prime Minister Tony Blair.
</P>
<P>
The three governments had asked German Daimler-Benz Aerospace,
Frence Aerospatiale and British Aerospace to come up with a
project for the reorganisation and integration of the sector.
</P>
<P>
The statement said "the Italian government had long hoped for
rapid development in the sector... to ensure efficiency and
competitiveness."
</P>
<P>
On the issue of defence, the Italian statement said:
"Integration at an European level is necessary if the sector is to
compete internationally and produce a clearly identifiable
European defence structure, essential to the political unification
of Europe."
</P>
<P>
It said the Italian government "favored and encouraged" the
integration efforts of Italian industries and was "closely
following" plans for the entry of Alenia, the Italian aerospace
company, into the Airbus consortium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
