<HEADLINE> Uruguay To Host Mini World Cup in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Uruguayan Football
Federation (AUF) said on Tuesday that Uruguay are set to host a
mini World Cup in the year of 2000 as the centerpiece of their
federation's centenary celebrations.
</P>
<P>
AUF planned to invite Argentina, Brazil, Italy for the
tournament while England, Germany and Spain may also take part.
</P>
<P>
AUF president and vice-president of the South American
Confederation Eugenio Figueredo proposed the idea to FIFA, the
world soccer governing body, during the recent under-17 World
Championship in Egypt.
</P>
<P>
In 1980 Uruguay invited Argentina, Brazil, Germany, Italy and
the Netherlands over to mark the 50th anniversary of the first
World Cup.
</P>
<P>
FIFA president Joao Havelange was to give AUF the go-ahead
though Italy's attempt to host a mini competition was turned down
several years ago. 
</P>
