<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Haikou Airport Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The Meilan International Airport in
Haikou, capital of the south China's island province of Hainan, is
scheduled to start operation by the end of next year.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the two-story main terminal has been completed,
with work on the main runway 3,600 meters long and 60 meter wide
and the installation of equipment on the approachway 3,600 meters
long and 44 meters wide is progressing smoothly. Some 80 percent
of the parking apron, which covers 128,000 sq.m., has been
completed.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the airport construction authority will focus on the
installation and testing of equipment, flight tests, and final
checks.
</P>
<P>
Meilan Airport, a project approved by the State Council, is
being constructed at a total cost of 2.3 billion yuan. The
facility will cover a total of 8,500 mu (one mu equals 0.067
ha). Key systems, including oil supply, power and terminal
facilities, as well as meteorology, computer, telecommunications and
flight systems, will reach advanced world levels.
</P>
<P>
Preparatory work for the airport began in November of 1995.
</P>
</TEXT>
