<HEADLINE> Myanmar Leader to Attend ASEAN Summit Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Myanmar State
Peace and Development Council and Prime Minister Senior-General
Than Shwe will attend the Second ASEAN Informal Summit scheduled
to open on December 14 in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, an official
announcement said here today.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first time for the Myanmar top leader to attend
a summit meeting of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN) since it was admitted into the grouping in July along with
Laos.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad,
Than Shwe will also attend an informal summit meeting of ASEAN
leaders and their counterparts from China, Japan and South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has been working closely with ASEAN, forming respective
committees and groups in all sectors and taking part in various
meetings and activities of the regional grouping since its
admission.  
</P>
