<HEADLINE> Argentina Issues Bond of $500 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Argentine government
issued Tuesday a bond of 500 million U.S. dollars for a five-year
term with an interest rate of 3.75 percent above the U.S.
Treasure Bond.
</P>
<P>
Under Secretary of Finance Miguel Kiguel told the press that out
of the 500-million-dollar revenues, 125 million dollars will go to
the 1997 budget, while the rest to the 1998 finance.
</P>
<P>
He said that 95 percent buyers of the new bond are institutional
investors from the United States while the remaining 5 percent
are from Europe and Argentina.
</P>
<P>
Argentina will need 17.4 billion dollars for its public
finance in 1998. 
</P>
