<HEADLINE> Cuba's Noted Revolutionary Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Cuba's noted revolutionary
Carlos Rafael Rodriguez Rodriguez died on Monday night at age of
84, the government reported.
</P>
<P>
Rodriguez took part in the Revolutionary Movement in
October 1930 and was an active fighter against the dictatorship
of Machado.
</P>
<P>
He was one of the most brilliant leaders of the People's
Socialist Party and co-founder of the Cuban Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
He was member of the first Central Committee and of the
Political Bureau from the first to the forth congress of the party.
</P>
<P>
Rodriguez was many times decorated in Cuba and in other
countries. 
