<HEADLINE> World Bank Supports Romania's Public Infrastructure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved a 25.5 million U.S. dollar loan in support of Romania's
ongoing privatization efforts, particularly in the real estate
sector.
</P>
<P>
The General Cadastre and Land Registration Project is designed
to facilitate the sustainable use of land and infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The project has two phases. First, it will concentrate on
implementation trials, training and technical assistance to lay
the foundation for the future surveying, mapping and land
registration that will take place in the second phase.
</P>
<P>
Since Romania joined the World Bank in 1972, it has received
from World Bank a total of 4.8 billion U.S. dollars for 52
projects. 
