has a successful visit," he said during his speech at the
National Press Club in Washington. "But, again, we have to wait
and see what the outcome is."
</P>
<P>
Richardson said demand for "continued, unfettered access by U.N.
inspectors to all sensitive sites in Iraq is nonnegotiable."
</P>
<P>
"Only then will this situation be resolved," he said.
